      • loadEagerly

        public ApiComposer.Builder loadEagerly(boolean loadEagerly)
        Determines if the interface implementation will be lazy or eager. By default the implementation will be lazy.

        If set to true the ApiComposer created from this builder will initialize the interface implementations immediately after the ApiComposer.compose(Class) is called.

        If set to false the ApiComposer.compose(Class) will only check the conditions for implementing the interface but will actually implement it when the request is called.

        Parameters:
        loadEagerly - the condition for whether the interface implementation should be lazy or eager
        Returns:
        A reference to the ApiComposer.Builder object
